description.narrative: In a year marked by the 30 CRC Anniversary, UNICEF communication and advocacy strategies contributed to position Early Childhood Development policies and Adolescents at the center of public agenda, with focus on Violence against Children (VAC), Gender Equality and Migrant Children, with a total reach of 24,3 million exposures in social media. UNICEF developed 10 media campaigns, reinforced 26 alliances including private sector and mobilized 100,500 adolescents. As a result of UNICEF initiatives 155 companies are aware of The Business Principles and Children's Rights and 24 are implementing specific actions to promote child rights within their value of chain. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
